      • isForceFullPage

        public boolean isForceFullPage()
        setForceFullPage(boolean)

      • setForceFullPage

        public void setForceFullPage(boolean forceFullPage)
        With forceFullPage=false we receive different pagination experience. Considering header for response Next-Offset which is the offset to request the next page. The Next-Offset is equivalent to Start-Index+limit, except on the last page. On the the last page, the Next-Offset is omitted to indicate there are no further pages.

        With forceFullPage=true enables full page pagination. Depending on the type of search and user permissions, this parameter can cause significant performance delays.
        Parameters:
        forceFullPage - accepts boolean value
